    "[…] Baker's Cyst: This is a fluid-filled cyst that forms behind the knee joint and is typically associated with knee joint effusions.",
    "It can be visible on MRI and may appear as a dark area within the effusion.Baker's cysts are usually hyperintense in T2weighted images and hypointense in T1weighted images and located in the popliteal fossa while communicating with the joint.",
